{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χρεία</b> <br /> (written <b>χρέα</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PCair.Zen.” 25.2, 148 (3rd c.BC))\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>], <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>χρείη</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Callias Epigrammaticus in “PSI” 11.1216.43 \">Refs</a>], ἡ: (χράομαι, κέχρημαι):— <b>need, want,</b> χρείας ὕπο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 287 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἵν᾽ ἕσταμεν χρείας considering in what great <b>need</b> we are, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1443 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χρείᾳ πολεμεῖν to war with <b>necessity,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “OC” 191 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs</a>]: with <i>genitive</i>, <b>want of</b>.., φαρμάκων χρείᾳ κατεσκέλλοντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 481; ἐν χρείᾳ τύχης [prev. author] “Th.” 506 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν χρείᾳ δορός in the <b>need</b> or <b>stress</b> of war, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 963; φορβῆς χρείᾳ [prev. author] “Ph.” 162 (_anapaest meter_), compare 1004: ἵππων ἡμῖν χρεία μὲν οὔτε τις πολλῶν οὔτε πολλή [ἐστιν] 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 834b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἦ μὴν ἔτ᾽ ἐμοῦ χρείαν ἕξει will have <b>need</b> of my help, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 170 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], cf. Call.[same place]; ἀφίκοντο εἰς χρείαν τῆς πόλεως came to feel <b>the need</b> of its assistance, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 244d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἰατρῶν ἐν χρείαις ἐσόμεθα, ἐν χρείᾳ ἡγεμόνος εἶναι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 373d, 566e; ὅτου σε χ. ἔχει 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 646 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so τίς χ. σ᾽ ἐμοῦ [ἔχει]; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 976, compare χρεώ 1.2: χρείαν ἔχω,\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] with <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Matt.3.14 \">NT</a>] (followed by (ίνα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.John.2.25); significations 1.1 and 111 in the same sentence, οὐχ οὕτως χ. ἔχομεν τῆς χ. παρὰ τῶν φίλων ὡς.. 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Gnomologium Vaticanum - Kleine Schriften” 34: proverbial, χ. διδάσκει, κἂν βραδύς τις ᾖ, σοφόν\">NT+4th c.BC+</a>] '<b>necessity</b> is the mother of invention', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 715, compare “El.” 376, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 263: _plural_, αἱ χρεῖαι τολμᾶν βιάζονται 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.2.1; αἱ τοῦ σώματος χ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.12.5; πρώτη γε καὶ μεγίστη τῶν χ. ἡ τῆς τροφῆς παρασκευή 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 369d; αἱ ἀναγκαῖαι χ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 23.148, compare 45.67 (_sing._); πολεμικαὶ χ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1328b11. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>want, poverty,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 175 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 420, etc.; διὰ τὴν χ. καὶ τὴν πενίαν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 534 (_anapaest meter_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>a request of necessity,</b> opposed to ἀξίωσις (a claim of merit), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.37, compare 33 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>request,</b> τὴν πρίν γε χ. ἠνύσασθ᾽ ἐμοῦ πάρα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 700 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κἀγὼ.. τοιάνδε σου χ. ἔχω make such <b>a request</b> of or to thee, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ch.” 481. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>business,</b> ὡς πρὸς τί χρεία; for what <b>purpose?</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1174, compare 1435; χρῆσθαί τινι χρείαν ἣν ἂν ἐθέλωσι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 868b; δοῦναι ἑαυτὸν εἰς τὴν χ. 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 8.16.11. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> especially <b>military</b> or <b>naval service,</b> ἡ πολεμικὴ χ. καὶ ἡ εἰρηνική the <b>employments</b> of war and of peace, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1254b32 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; αἱ κατὰ θάλατταν [χ.], ἡ ἐν τῇ γῇ χ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.52.1, 31.21.3 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; οἱ ἐπὶ τῶν χ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Aristeas 110, LXX.1Mac.12.45; οἱ πρὸς ταῖς χ. LXX.Jdt.12.10; οἱ ἐπὶ χρειῶν τεταγμένοι “BGU” 543.1 (1st c.BC)\">LXX+1st c.BC+</a>]; in military sense, <b>action, engagement,</b> αἱ κατὰ μέρος χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.84.7, +others \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.c</b></Level4> generally, <b>business, employment, function,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.45.2, etc.\">Refs</a>]; ἡ ἐγκεχειρισμένη χ. the <b>duty</b> assigned, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 741.11 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; οὓς καταστήσομεν ἐπὶ τῆς χ. ταύτης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Act.6.3; χ. πολιτικαί 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Marius” 32, etc. \">NT+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.d</b></Level4> <b>a business, affair, matter,</b> like{χρέος}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 2.49.9, +others\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; τὴν ὑπὲρ τούτων χ. the <b>study</b> of these things, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.29U. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.e</b></Level4> χ. ἀναγκαία <b>need</b> of nature, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 4.33; τροφῆς χ. 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.472. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>use,</b> <br /><Level3><b>__III.1</b></Level3> as a property, <b>use, advantage, service,</b> χρείης εἵνεκα μηδεμιῆς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 62; τῆς χ. τοῦ παιδὸς ἀποστερηθῆναι 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.3.4; ἡ χ. τῆς ῥητορικῆς 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 480a; πωλοῦντες τὴν τῆς ἰσχύος χ. [prev. author] “R.” 371e \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; χρείαν ἔχειν τοῖς ἀνθρώποις to be <b>of service</b> to mankind, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Smp.” 204c \">Refs</a>]; τὰ οὐδὲν εἰς χρείαν things of no <b>use</b> or <b>service,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator “Prooemia” 56.3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; χρείαν ἔχει εἴς τι is of <b>service</b> towards.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC(?): Sosipater Comicus 1.41; for 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 725, see at {ἐρευνάω} 1: _plural_, χρεῖαι.. φίλων ἀνδρῶν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>services rendered</b> by them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 8.42 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χρείας παρέχεσθαι render <b>services,</b> Decrees cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.84, “IG” 22.654.15, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.16.8 (_sing._)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἵνα σοι τὰς χ. παρέσχωμαι (sic) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PCair.Zen.” 498 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; μεγάλην παρεῖχε χ. τοῖς κοινοῖς πράγμασιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.97.4 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; παρέχειν χ. to be <b>serviceable, useful,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Aristo Stoic. 1.79; ἑξήκοντα καὶ τριακόσια χρειῶν γένη παρέχον δένδρον 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.724e; χ. ναυτικαί \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<b>equipments,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 2.10. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> as an action, <b>using, use,</b> κτῆσις καὶ χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.4.1, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 451c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν χρείᾳ εἶναι in <b>use,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phd.” 87c \">Refs</a>]; κατὰ τὴν χ. for <b>use,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “R.” 330c; πρὸς τὴν ἀνθρωπίνην χ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.2.25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ χ. τῶν λόγων the <b>employment</b> of words, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 239d, compare “Plt.” 272d: _plural_, λάμπει γὰρ ἐν χρείαισιν ὥσπερ.. χαλκός\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] is made bright by <b>constant use,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 864. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> of persons, <b>familiarity, intimacy,</b> τινος <b>with</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.63 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>any relation of business</b> or <b>intercourse,</b> ἐν χρείᾳ τινὶ τῇ πρὸς ἀλλήλους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 372a; ἡ πρὸς ἀλλήλους χ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1376b13; [Νικόμαχος] συνεβίω Ἀμυντᾳ.. ἰατροῦ καὶ φίλου χρείᾳ \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>in the relationship, capacity,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 5.1. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> Rhet., <b>pregnant sentence, maxim,</b> frequently illustrated by an anecdote, Sen.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Ep.” 33.7, 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “προγυμνάσματα” 3, Aphthon, “Prog.” 3, 1st-2nd c.AD(?): Theon Rhetor “Progymnasmata - Rhet.” 5, etc.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, title of works by Zeno [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 6.91), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristippus Philosophus, etc.; by 3rd c.BC: Macho Comicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], a collection of sayings of courtesans, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 13.577d; ἡ τοῦ Κλεομένους χ. 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.218a; χρεῖαι καὶ ἱστορίαι [prev. work]78f. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5532","accentedUnicode":"χρεία","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0888","matchingForm":"ἀχρεῖος","stepTransliteration":"achreios","gloss":"worthless","_zh_tw_Gloss":"無用","_es_Gloss":"inútil","_zh_Gloss":"无用"},{"strongNumber":"G5530","matchingForm":"χράω","stepTransliteration":"chraō","gloss":"to use","_zh_tw_Gloss":"用","_es_Gloss":"usar","_zh_Gloss":"用"},{"strongNumber":"G5534","matchingForm":"χρή","stepTransliteration":"chrē","gloss":"to ought/need","_zh_tw_Gloss":"應當","_es_Gloss":"deber/necesitar","_zh_Gloss":"应当"},{"strongNumber":"G5535","matchingForm":"χρῄζω","stepTransliteration":"chrēzō","gloss":"to need","_zh_tw_Gloss":"所需用","_es_Gloss":"necesitar","_zh_Gloss":"所需用"}],"shortDef":"need, necessity","mediumDef":"<b>use; need, necessity, requisiteness,</b> <ref='Eph.4.29'>Eph. 4:29;</ref> <ref='Heb.7.11'>Heb. 7:11;</ref> personal <b>need, an</b> individual <b>want,</b> <ref='Act.20.34'>Acts 20:34;</ref> <ref='Rom.12.13'>Rom. 12:13;</ref> <ref='Php.2.25'>Phil. 2:25;</ref> 4:16, 19; <greek>χρειαν ἔχω</greek>, <b>to need, require, want,</b> <ref='Mat.6.8; 14:16'>Mt. 6:8; 14:16</ref>; <ref='Mrk.2.25'>Mk. 2:25</ref>; <ref='Jhn.2.25'>Jn. 2:25</ref>; <greek>ἐστὶ χρεια</greek>, <b>there is need,</b> <ref='Luk.10.42'>Lk. 10:42</ref>; <greek>τὰ πρὸς τὴν χρειαν</greek>, <b>necessary things,</b> <ref='Act.28.10'>Acts 28:10;</ref> <b>a necessary business, affair,</b> <ref='Act.6.3'>Acts 6:3</ref>","stepGloss":"need","stepTransliteration":"chreia","count":49,"_es_Definition":"necesidad ; necesidad, deseo, falta ; deber, tarea, función (HCH.6:3) ; tener necesidad de algo o alguien","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 需求, 應有的 (有別於個人的需求)<br>2) 需求, 匱乏, 困難<br>3) 缺少因而必要的事 (弗 4:29)<br>4) 職責, 職位 (徒 6:3)","_zh_Definition":"1) 需求, 应有的 (有别于个人的需求)<br>2) 需求, 匮乏, 困难<br>3) 缺少因而必要的事 (弗 4:29)<br>4) 职责, 职位 (徒 6:3)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"nhu cầu","_zh_tw_Gloss":"需要, 用, 需","_es_Gloss":"necesidad","_zh_Gloss":"需要, 用, 需"}]}